# Project Phoenix coding rules

## Source-of-truth order
1. User task · 2. Governance in **`AGENTS.md`** read-first table · 3. `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md` · 4. old plans

## Read first when relevant
Full file list: **`AGENTS.md`** table. **Read-first pass** before: flags/env; caches / fetch / React Query; modal chunk/shell/load; frontend–backend contracts.

## Architecture
Smallest reversible change. Logic in services/adapters/controllers; thin UI and routes. Extend existing modules. Align `IAdapter` + API in one change.

## Flags
Modal/composer flags: update `00-flag-contract.md` and `99-cleanup-ledger.md`. No orphan temp flags.

## Query / cache / fetch
Reuse query keys, hooks, timing. No duplicate state (React + context + RQ) for the same server data. Backend response caching only with evidence + rollback.

## Validation
`npm run lint` · `typecheck` · `test` · `build` · `build:server` if server changed
